## 🔴 Security Bug Discovered and Fixed

### SEC-BUG-001: Refresh Token Reuse Allowed (High Severity)

**File:** [auth.py](file:///C:/Users/joshu/OneDrive/Documents/Project/Inventory%20Management%20System/backend/app/api/v1/auth.py)

**Description:** The `POST /api/v1/auth/refresh` endpoint blacklisted the old refresh token after use BUT never checked if the incoming token was already on the blacklist **before** issuing new tokens.

**Impact:** A stolen refresh token could be reused indefinitely to issue new access tokens, completely bypassing the token rotation security model.

**Fix Applied:**
```python
# Added before the blacklist-and-issue logic in auth.py:
already_used = await redis.get(f"blacklist:{body.refresh_token}")
if already_used:
    raise HTTPException(
        status_code=status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED,
        detail="Refresh token has already been used. Please log in again.",
    )
```

**Test that caught it:** `TestAuthenticationSecurity::test_refresh_token_reuse_rejected`

